=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Couple enantiopure 2-fluoro-6-methylaniline with enantiopure 1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,8-naphthyridine-3-carboxylic acid (matching the target’s ring stereocenter; e.g., HATU/DIPEA or acid chloride) to give the bicyclic carboxamide intermediate ArNHC(=O)-[chiral tetrahydro-1,8-naphthyridine] with the ring N left free. | Step 2: Couple that ring NH with Boc-protected 2-amino-2-(tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)acetic acid of the required configuration (Boc-NH-CH(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)-CO2H) to form Boc-protected amino amide BocNH-CH(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)-C(=O)N([tetrahydro-1,8-naphthyridine amide]). | Step 3: Remove Boc (TFA) to give the free amine H2N-CH(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)-C(=O)N([tetrahydro-1,8-naphthyridine amide]). | Step 4: Acylate this amine with Boc-N-methyl-L-alanine (or its activated ester/acid chloride) to give BocNH(CH3)CH(CH3)C(=O)NH-CH(tetrahydropyran-4-yl)-C(=O)N([tetrahydro-1,8-naphthyridine amide]). | Step 5: Final Boc deprotection furnishes CN[C@@H](C)C(=O)N[C@H](C(=O)N1c2ncccc2C[C@H]1C(=O)Nc1c(C)cccc1F)C1CCOCC1.

